Korean Firms Form $97 Million Renewable Energy Guarantee Fund

-- B y   S a n g i m   H a n
-- 
2011-09-01T03:05:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-01/korean-firms-form-97-million-renewable-energy-guarantee-fund.html
Korea Electric Power Corp. (KEP)  and
industrial and financial groups contributed a combined 103
billion won ($97 million) to provide guarantees to small-sized
companies involved in renewable energy, the Ministry of
Knowledge Economy said in an e-mailed statement today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sangim Han in Seoul at 
